kes it that much worse!\n8 out of 9 found this helpful. Was this review helpful? Sign in to vote.\nPermalink'),(1123,67,'9/10','Funny Second Movie','katerinammurray','4 June 2024','The critical reviews of Kevin Harts second movie, \"Die Hart 2\", are surprising to me. Amidst the vast landscape of contemporary low-budget films, the movie stands high in my book as a continuation of established comedic themes and narrative contours from its first film and is on theme with Kevin Hart\'s content. Viewers acquainted with the first film are likely to recognize a nuanced familiarity with the comedic tonality and overall ambiance characterizing the sequel. Looking at it from the entertainment and humor angle, the movie kept me engaged with its humor and storyline. The cliffhanger at the end leaves me eager for more, sparking hopes for a third movie in the series.\n4 out of 11 found this helpful. Was this review helpful? Sign in to vote.\nPermalink'),(1124,67,'7/10','Are movie watchers getting too Hart to satisfy? (See what i did...lol)','destroyerwod','2 June 2024','Everytime before a review i go and check a few of the previous reviews just to see the general feeling of peoples and often, just in this case, i see a ton of super negative reviews like 1 or 2 out of 10 and i just ask myself why?\n\nIs this the greatest comedy of all time? No. Is this the greatest action movie of all time? No. Its a Kevin Hart movie on a streaming platform in the vain of a self parody (Kevin Hart plays an exagerated version of himself).\n\nI wasn\'t expecting this to be a memorable movie. All i wanted was to have some fun for a one time watch with a few beers and move on. Thats exactly what i got.\n\nI am a movie fan, i watch 150 movies a year, wich 90%+ are movies i never saw. Yet i know my \"style\" of movies and i try to go to watch what i enjoy. There is plenty of movies peoples give great reviews wich i know they ain\'t my type of movies, so if i do decide to watch them i keep that in mind 